               <children>
                  <TextArea maxHeight="1.7976931348623157E308" maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308" text="This application was made as a school project to support physicist in research &#10;at the Commenius University in Slovakia. &#10;&#10;Application is free-to-use, open-source, and works with machine HP4191a. &#10;&#10;Project was built with Java 11 (maven) and Scenebuilder (javaFX). &#10;Dependency -  https://github.com/TIS2020-FMFI/hpctrl&#10;&#10;Credits belong to: &#10;Jakub Zak, Maryia Pikuleva, Richard Nagy, Jan Pastorek, Pavel Petrovic(supervisor)&#10;&#10;-- Connect to the machine --&#10;Machine tries to automatically connect GPIB, which can fail if hpctrl.exe&#10;is not on the correct adress/path within project. If this happens, you should check if the path&#10;is correct and if it is, try to connect manually by clicking on the GPIB connection button &#10;or try to restart the app. &#10;&#10;-- Measurement --&#10;- runs by pressing run button, which also triggers graph visualization&#10;  * before pressing run you can set measurement input &#10;    parameters on the left and choose measured quantity below the graph&#10;  * if autosweep is ON, the measurement will run automatically, &#10;    if it is OFF, the measurement will continue by one step if you click on the next button&#10;- can be loaded into a graph by pressing the LOAD button below the graph&#10;- can be saved using SAVE AS button, used parameters and comment will be also saved &#10;- can be exported by using EXPORT button, created file contains solely measured values&#10;&#10;-- Graph functionality --&#10;- press ALT and drag mouse to pan a chart&#10;- press ALT and wheel up/down mouse to zoom a chart&#10;- select with mouse some part of the chart to zoom in&#10;- zoom back with draging to up-left corner&#10;- save graph as an image by right-clicking and select export as&#10;- you can click on the point to see its value better with crosshair&#10;&#10;-- Calibration --&#10;- calibration can be done by pressing on the calibration button and calibration window&#10;   will pop up&#10;&#10;Repository of this project and contacts can be found here&#10;https://github.com/TIS2020-FMFI/hp&#10;&#10;HP 4191a Manual&#10;https://doc.xdevs.com/doc/HP_Agilent_Keysight/HP%204191A%20Operation%20&amp;%20Service.pdf&#10;&#10;" VBox.vgrow="ALWAYS" />
               </children>
            </VBox>
            <HBox fx:id="actionContainer" alignment="CENTER" minHeight="50.0" prefHeight="70.0" prefWidth="200.0">
